KATSINA â€“ Katsina State Governor Aminu Bello Masari has declared Monday 11th of April 2022 as a Work Free day to enable workers and their families to exercise their franchise in the upcoming Local Government Election. This is contained in a press statement signed by the Permanent Secretary, Administration, Office of the Head Of Civil Service, Alhaji Usman Isyaku, and made available to newsmen in Katsina on Friday. According to the statement, the one-day public holiday declared is to enable civil servants and their families to travel to their constituencies to cast their votes. The statement, therefore, urged workers to utilize the opportunity to peacefully exercise their constitutional rights by voting for candidates of their choice.